<p>"California Gov. Jerry Brown rose to the bait, dismissing Perry&rsquo;s paltry radio ad buy as not even &ldquo;a burp; it&rsquo;s barely a fart.&rdquo;</p>
<p>And now this: <strong>California GOP's convention headliner? Rick Perry</strong>.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/08/19/rick-perry-to-headline-california-gop-convention-in-october/">http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/08/19/rick-perry-to-headline-california-gop-convention-in-october/</a></p>
<p>Gotta love it!</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78387761,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;favedave&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">6 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78387761" title="Link to this comment">#8</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 3:17 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78389444"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78389444,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;mindbend&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;MindBend&quot;}"></div><a name="star25"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star26" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://mindbend.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://mindbend.newsvine.com/">MindBend</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78389444" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Perry's doing the same thing in New York and Illinois. (Lewis Black did an awesome bit on The Daily Show about this)  I can't wait to see the next ad:  Bring your business to Texas where your taxes will be so low we can't even afford paved roads".</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78389444,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;mindbend&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">22 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78389444" title="Link to this comment">#8.1</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 4:18 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78390938"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390938,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-saintmichaelangelo&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Michael Cruise-4132159&quot;}"></div><a name="star26"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star27" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://fb-saintmichaelangelo.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=null4EACA299-07E8-7880-7048-C307B3A5A416.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://fb-saintmichaelangelo.newsvine.com/">Michael Cruise-4132159</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78390938" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I encountered some yokel yesterday that was crowing about the millions of people fleeing blue states and heading for greener pastures in states like Texas.  First, green is not a color you will ever find in the state of 1000 shades of tan.  Second...millions?  Pure anecdotal dogshyte.  Third and finally...so I guess that would be pushing Texas blue even quicker than predicted, eh?</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390938,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;fb-saintmichaelangelo&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">8 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78390938" title="Link to this comment">#8.2</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 5:17 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78392800"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78392800,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;cloie46&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;cloie46&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://cloie46.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=cloie46A0990709-EBA1-DEB2-DDAB-785939BBE57D.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://cloie46.newsvine.com/">cloie46</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78392800" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>I moved to the DFW area 4 months ago to be closer to part of my family--and to help turn it blue I kid.  I have been amazed and dismayed at all the highway construction going on in this area all at the same time (4 freeways that I have encountered so far and one toll road.)  I assumed the money came from the Federal general funds and from "stimulus" programs that the reds here disdain so much. In two places I have seen roads that had to have been built on the theory "build it they will come" maybe. I've also mused that this is the way they keep employment figures up.</p>
<p>As a Californian, I laugh at what is considered rush hour traffic. I only avoid the horrid construction zones with missing signs and single lanes even the natives complain about.</p>
<p>Lastly, the freeways I do travel are open enough for drag racing and cutting in and out of lanes, and tailgating for fun.  How do so many young white males get away with it? (As a whitey myself I can make this comment!) I think it might be that there is no highway patrol in populated Texas. Local police forces cities are responsible for freeway portions in their own town.  There is a state patrol for rural areas but I guess Texas will be needing fewer of those as they convert rural roads to gravel.</p>
<p>I advise all those red-necks in the boonies explore the DFW area to see where the road money is being spent.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78392800,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;cloie46&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78392800" title="Link to this comment">#8.3</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 6:51 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /></div><div class="commentcontainer"><span></span></div></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody " id="c78387783"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78387783,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;miracle&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Miracle&quot;}"></div><a name="star27"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star28" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://miracle.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=miracleEB60B15A-1B73-210D-C05D-B595BA54649A.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://miracle.newsvine.com/">Miracle</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78387783" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>The damage to a road in in proportion to the fourth power of the axle load of the vehicles that drive on it. Look at diesel taxes and look at gasoline taxes. We generally subsidize heavy truck traffic, but we do it in exchange for the economic benefit they bring. Because you still have to attract customers, that's why the roads around malls and businesses districts are generally in pretty good shape. Less so in industrial zones. But out in the boonies, nobody but the locals see the damage and the goods these trucks haul aren't going to suffer from a few potholes. This isn't unique to Texas. Texas is just seeing it on a large scale.</p>
<p>Business has, for the last few decades, been slacking off on their part of the social contract.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78387783,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;miracle&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">23 votes</div></li></ul></div><img class="replybutton" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_reply_mini.gif" width="35" height="12" alt="Reply" /><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78387783" title="Link to this comment">#9</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 3:17 PM EDT</span><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78390089"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390089,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;zora&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Zora Renee&quot;}"></div><a name="star28"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star29" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://zora.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://zora.newsvine.com/">Zora Renee</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78390089" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Yes, but they've been aided and abetted by politicians that people put into office.  And now no longer feel obligated to anything except their own bottom line.  Yet another reason to vote those GOTP puppies out!</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390089,