<p>We are 70T in debt after unfunded liabilities.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>How much debt is a baby born with, once you account for unfunded liabilities such as lifetime food, shelter, clothing, education, and medical care?</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78389285,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dcsessions&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">6 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78389285" title="Link to this comment">#14.3</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 4:12 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78389671"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78389671,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;taylo019&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Taylo019&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://taylo019.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://taylo019.newsvine.com/">Taylo019</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78389671" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Do any of you understand the math associated with our debt?  We are headed for a financial collapse.  China is already looking for ways outside the dollar as it relates to their oil trade.  Just look at our stock market.  We are hanging on by consumer confidence.  Billionaires are dumping all their US stock.  And our response is to flood the market with even more cash. </p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78389671,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;taylo019&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78389671" title="Link to this comment">#14.4</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 4:27 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78390081"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390081,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;bginchi&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;BGinCHI&quot;}"></div><a name="star37"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star38" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://bginchi.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://bginchi.newsvine.com/">BGinCHI</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78390081" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>You are really getting your money's worth out of those newsletters.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390081,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;bginchi&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">6 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78390081" title="Link to this comment">#14.5</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 4:43 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78390466"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390466,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;taylo019&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Taylo019&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://taylo019.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://taylo019.newsvine.com/">Taylo019</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78390466" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Yeah your probably right, what do economics professors and billionaires know anyway about this kind of stuff?  In 08 they were just lucky.  </p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78390466,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;taylo019&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">1 vote</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78390466" title="Link to this comment">#14.6</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 4:57 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78391070"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78391070,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;rick2502410&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Rick-2502410&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://rick2502410.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://rick2502410.newsvine.com/">Rick-2502410</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78391070" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
<p>How much debt is a baby born with, once you account for unfunded liabilities such as lifetime food, shelter, clothing, education, and medical care</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, if you start using the word "debt" to describe a lot of things that are not debt, sure, the amount of "debt" skyrockets.  Ordinarily the word is used to describe "money that has been borrowed and will be repaid."  It doesn't mean "costs that will have to be paid at some point in the future."  Because, well, that has nothing to do with whether money has been loaned or borrowed.</p></p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78391070,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;rick2502410&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78391070" title="Link to this comment">#14.7</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 5:23 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78391644"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78391644,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;miracle&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Miracle&quot;}"></div><a name="star38"></a><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="#star39" class="noborder star"><img src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/b_star.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="" title="Jump To Next Highly Rated Comment" /></a><a href="http://miracle.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=miracleEB60B15A-1B73-210D-C05D-B595BA54649A.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://miracle.newsvine.com/">Miracle</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78391644" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Taylo019, I wouldn't be talking about economics professors and all that if you haven't even read what Adam Smith said about fiat vs. specie currency back in 1776.</p>
<p>Gold (or silver) has no value beyond its inherent usefulness. It is dead stock. Fiat money is simply an abstraction of the value of goods and labor in the market. But you guys don't understand abstractions very well. If you did, you'd understand that those unfunded liabilities are the same as any other pension system, based upon future investment returns. Since the investment they are making is in the continued success of the American economy, they're pretty secure. Unless somebody does something really stupid like, oh, refusing to pay the bills by not raising the debt limit and trashing our good credit built over 230 years. That's what will take down Social Security and all the money you have invested in it.</p>
<p>Billionaires are billion-aires in what? Cheese doodles? There isn't enough mineable gold and silver in this world to supply the world economy with a Mises-friendly Austrian 100% reserve currency without contracting the economy because trade velocity would ground to a halt. You live in a fantasy world.</p>
<p>I can understand survivalist loons being goldbugs. They're constantly worried that the world is going to hell in the next generation. Just like granddaddy said. And his granddaddy a'fore 'im. It's the conservatives who like to call themselves patriots that puzzle me. Always betting against the country they claim to love.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78391644,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;miracle&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">7 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78391644" title="Link to this comment">#14.8</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 5:53 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78392184"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78392184,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dcsessions&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;D. C. Sessions&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://dcsessions.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=DCSessions4F464B56-7189-A0BE-BB34-AFC6858536F2.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://dcsessions.newsvine.com/">D. C. Sessions</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78392184" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
<p>Yeah your probably right, what do economics professors and billionaires  know anyway about this kind of stuff?  In 08 they were just lucky.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>You mean the ones who were predicting hyperinflation in 2009, and they got lucky that it didn't happen?  The ones who wiped their brows in relief and then predicted hyperinflation in 2010?  And when that didn't happen predicted hyperinflation in 2011, 2012, and 2013?  Those experts?</p>
<p>I agree -- they've been very lucky.</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78392184,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dcsessions&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">3 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78392184" title="Link to this comment">#14.9</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 6:19 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78392238"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78392238,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dcsessions&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;D. C. Sessions&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://dcsessions.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://m.static.newsvine.com/servista/imagesizer?file=DCSessions4F464B56-7189-A0BE-BB34-AFC6858536F2.jpg&width=60" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="false" /></a><a href="http://dcsessions.newsvine.com/">D. C. Sessions</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78392238" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><blockquote>
<p>Do any of you understand the math associated with our debt?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yes.  And the fact that you can't answer <a href="20092412-a-different-kind-of-stone-age?threadId=3797169&amp;commentId=78392184#c78389285" title="Link to this comment">#14.3</a> tells me you don't.  Or perhaps do, but answering wouldn't serve your agenda.</p>
<p>So I'll put it another way to hammer the point home: using the same accounting methods that got you that $70T number, what is the debt including unfunded liabilities for the US private sector?</p></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_MiniToolbox"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78392238,&quot;threadId&quot;:&quot;3797169&quot;,&quot;contentId&quot;:&quot;20092412&quot;,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;dcsessions&quot;}"></div><ul class="list"><li class="box votes"><div class="label">2 votes</div></li></ul></div><span class="commentdate"><a href="#c78392238" title="Link to this comment">#14.10</a> - Mon Aug 19, 2013 6:21 PM EDT</span></div></div></div><div class="vine-p p-comment_Comment showAvatars commentbody child " id="c78392622"><div class="printerData hide" data-printer="{&quot;commentId&quot;:78392622,&quot;authorDomain&quot;:&quot;taylo019&quot;,&quot;authorDisplayName&quot;:&quot;Taylo019&quot;}"></div><div class="c_author"><div class="normal"><a href="http://taylo019.newsvine.com/"><img class="comment_author_avatar" src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/_/blank.gif" data-avatar_src="http://www.cdn.newsvine.com/_vine/images/av/60x60/msnbc.jpg" width="35" height="35" alt="Comment author avatar" data-is_default_avatar="true" /></a><a href="http://taylo019.newsvine.com/">Taylo019</a></div></div><div id="commentText_78392622" class="c_text"><div class="normal"><div class="commentSource"><p>Im not betting, its simple math.  We are in a unique position where we can make more money anytime we desire.  We owe more than we can pay back without making more money. eventually one of our debtors is going to say they are no longer doing business with a country who de-values its own currency and the dollar will fall.</p>
